ylvania]] guarded the corps trains, and was not engaged in the battle.</ref>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Joseph B. Carr]] ('''w''')\n|\n* [[1st Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|1st Massachusetts]]: Ltc Clark B. Baldwin ('''w'''), Maj Gardner Walker ('''w''')\n* [[11th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|11th Massachusetts]]: Ltc Porter D. Tripp, Maj Andrew N. McDonald ('''w''')\n* [[16th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|16th Massachusetts]]: Ltc Waldo Merriam ('''w''', July 2), Cpt Matthew Donovan\n* [[12th New Hampshire Volunteer Infantry|12th New Hampshire]]: Cpt John F. Langley ('''w'''), Cpt Thomas E. Barker\n* [[11th New Jersey Volunteer Infantry Regiment|11th New Jersey]]: Col Robert McAllister ('''w'''), Maj Philip J. Kearny ('''mw'''), Cpt Luther Martin ('''k'''), Lt John Schoonover ('''w'''), Cpt William H. Lloyd ('''w'''), Cpt Samuel T. Sleeper, Lt John Schoonover\n* [[26th Pennsylvania Infantry|26th Pennsylvania]]: Maj Robert L. Bodine ('''w''')\n|-\n| [[Excelsior Brigade|2nd Brigade]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[William R. Brewster]]\n|\n* [[70th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|70th New York]]: Col John E. Farnum\n* [[71st New York Infantry|71st New York]]: Col Henry L. Potter ('''w''')\n* [[72nd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|72nd New York]]: Col John S. Austin ('''w'''), Ltc John Leonard, Maj Caspar K. Abell\n* [[73rd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|73rd New York]]: Maj Michael W. Burns\n* [[74th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|74th New York]]: Ltc Thomas Holt\n* [[120th New York Volunteer Infantry|120th New York]]: Ltc Cornelius D. Westbrook ('''w''', July 2), Maj John R. Tappen\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[George C. Burling]]\n|\n* [[2nd New Hampshire Volunteer Regiment|2nd New Hampshire]]: Col Edward L. Bailey ('''w'''), Ltc James W. Carr ('''w''')\n* [[5th New Jersey Volunteer Infantry|5th New Jersey]]: Col [[William J. Sewell]] ('''w'''), Cpt Thomas C. Godfrey, Cpt Henry H. Woolsey ('''w''')\n* 