. The Second Brigade left in the Department of Washington</ref>\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Samuel W. Crawford]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[William McCandless]]\n|\n* [[1st Pennsylvania Reserve Regiment|1st Pennsylvania Reserves]] (9 companies): Col William C. Talley ('''w''')\n* [[2nd Pennsylvania Reserve Regiment|2nd Pennsylvania Reserves]]: Ltc George A. Woodward\n* [[6th Pennsylvania Reserve Regiment|6th Pennsylvania Reserves]]: Ltc Wellington H. Ent\n* [[13th Pennsylvania Reserve Regiment|13th Pennsylvania Reserves]]: Col Charles F. Taylor ('''k'''), Ltc Alanson E. Niles ('''w''') Maj William R. Hartshorne\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Joseph W. Fisher]]\n|\n* [[5th Pennsylvania Reserve Regiment|5th Pennsylvania Reserves]]: Ltc George Dare, Maj James H. Larrimer\n* [[9th Pennsylvania Reserve Regiment|9th Pennsylvania Reserves]]: Ltc James M. Snodgrass\n* [[10th Pennsylvania Reserve Regiment|10th Pennsylvania Reserves]]: Col [[Adoniram J. Warner]] ('''w'''), Ltc James B. Knox\n* [[11th Pennsylvania Reserve Regiment|11th Pennsylvania Reserves]]: Col Samuel M. Jackson, Ltc Daniel Porter ('''w''')\n* [[12th Pennsylvania Reserve Regiment|12th Pennsylvania Reserves]] (9 companies): Col [[Martin Davis Hardin]]\n|-\n|\n| Artillery Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCpt [[Augustus P. Martin]]\n|\n* [[3rd Massachusetts Light Artillery|Massachusetts Light, 3rd Battery]]: Lt Aaron F. Walcott\n* [[Battery C, 1st New York Light Artillery|1st New York Light, Battery C]]: Cpt Almont Barnes\n* [[Battery L, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery L]]: Cpt Frank C. Gibbs\n* [[5th U.S. Artillery, Battery D|5th United States, Battery D]]: Lt [[Charles E. Hazlett]] ('''k'''), Lt [[Benjamin F. Rittenhouse]]\n* [[5th U.S. Artillery, Battery I|5th United States, Battery I]]: Lt Malbone F. Watson ('''w'''), Lt Charles C. MacConnell\n|}\n\n===[[VI Corps (Union Army)|VI Corps]]===\nMG [[John Sedgwick]]\n\nGeneral Headquarters:\n* 1st New Jersey Cavalr